    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-13T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-13T15:00:00-05:00" n="549"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/196: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-13T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 13, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>204. Chile is virtually without a Government this afternoon. The armed forces are
                    divided with <persName corresp="#p_MRR1">Merino</persName> leading one side and
                        <persName corresp="#p_LCP1">Lagos</persName> the other. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MRR1">Merino</persName> is openly against foreign, particularly
                    American, interests. The civilians are hoping to profit from the division in the
                    armed forces. <persName corresp="#p_DCG1">Dávila</persName> is still in the
                    Moneda and has the support of <persName corresp="#p_LCP1">Lagos</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_BEGB1">General Blanche</persName>. The only
                    characteristic of the present situation is confusion. Up to the present there
                    have been no disorders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
